  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: fa89f721cc4232d4693acd45ffd5844d, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCInteraction
  interactPrompt: {fileID: 1297337227}
  dialogueBox: {fileID: 1492002820}
  dialogueText: {fileID: 1758709719}
  questCanvas: {fileID: 362686213}
  trashContainer: {fileID: 1031861459}
  dialogueLines:
  - "Hey there, traveler! I\u2019m so glad you\u2019re here. Look around... this
    place used to be beautiful, but now it's covered in junk!"
  - To fix this, we need to understand the three types of waste. Biodegradable waste
    is stuff that can rot and turn back into soil. Non-biodegradable waste stays
    around for a long, long time, and Recyclable items are things we can turn into
    something brand new! If we segregate properly, we keep our home healthy!
  - I need your help. Can you go around and collect the trash? You'll need to decide
    which bin each item belongs in. Is it something that rots, something that stays
    forever, or something we can reuse?
  - "But be careful! If you put trash in the wrong bin, it causes a big mess. For
    every 3 mistakes you make, I\u2019ll have to deduct some of your Gold to pay
    for the cleanup."
  - 'Ready or not, here we go! Your first Eco Quest is now active: Collect and correctly
    sort 9 pieces of waste scattered across this field. Watch your bins closely,
    keep your mistakes low to protect your Gold'
